With clustering coming in 2.3, we can no longer use the file system as a reliable storage medium for binary data. Attachments are the next best thing - for space specific stuff we can attach to the SpaceDescriptor, however there is no where to put binary data which is globally unique (unrelated to a space).

A "Confluence" (or better named) CEO is required which, like SpaceDescriptor, has no UI to list / modify the attachments on.

Other suggestions are welcome, but this seems the most viable.

