It would be nice if the {children} macro could allow the same choice of displays as {toc}, i.e. a "type" parameter which would allow to display children on the same line instead of hierarchically, and a "separator" parameter to choose a separating character between children listed.

An example would be:

{children:type=flat|separator=pipe}

The result would look like this:

Link_to_Child1 | Link_to_Child2 | Link_to_Child3 | etc.

When trying to include an excerpt from a news page, excerpt-include macro complains that it cannot find the page. For example

{noformat}
{excerpt-include:/2006/12/21/News page name}
{noformat}

The same page address works for links and other purposes, but not with excerpt-include (or include macro).

If there is another way to access excerpts from a news item (like you can with blog-posts macro), we would like to know it. We need it for a custom user macro that replaces blog-posts. Currently we're using $post.excerpt but this results in a bunch of text taken directly from the beginning of the news item.

